notesStmt.note: Illegible Hebrew inscription, undated (on the upper part of folio 1r).
Includes a table of moladot (lunation-commencements) for the period 1279/80 - 1295/95 (folio 444r).
Manuscript description based on Margoliouth, G.: Catalogue of the Hebrew and Samaritan Manuscripts in the British Museum, London 1965.

msContents.summary: Miscellany of biblical and other texts ('The Northern French Miscellany' or earlier 'the British Museum Miscellany'): including the Pentateuch, Hafṭarot, Tiḳun Soferim, Five Scrolls, prayer book for the entire year with Hagadah, legal texts, poetry, calendars, the book of Tobit in Hebrew, etc.

layoutDesc.layout: Columns: 1 2; ruled lines: 36 40; written lines: 35 39; Ruling is visible. Hair-side and flesh-side of the folios are not distinguishable. Many marginal illuminations and illustrations, which consist mainly of letters and designs, in colors or in colors and gold.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Ashkenazi (French) square and semi-cursive script, partially punctuated. Written by Binyamin: inscribed with his name (folios 142v, 306v, 514r, 535r), the name Binyamin is marked in the text (folios 24v, 26r).

binding.p: Pre-1600. Dark brown leather over wooden boards, gold tooled.

history.provenance: Acquisition: M. Reina of Milan: sold to the booksellers Payne & Foss in Paris in 1838 or 1839 for the British Museum: note by Frederic Madden that it was 'Purchased of MM. Payne & Foss 13th July, 1839. It came from the collection of M. Reina of Milan, sold at Paris in 1839' (folio 746v).
